::The horse seemed to nod as it reared in triumph and clopped out into the forests.  The group rode night, make camp and broke camp at the next rise of the moon.  It was approaching the hour of midnight and Shey's castle loomed in the distance.  A small river that could have been a stream was the only thing that styreaked the land with color.  Anya stopped as they reached the bluff and Shey turned to her companions.::<br>
